==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Frankly
<hw>Frank"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In a frank manner;
freely.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Very <qex>frankly</qex> he confessed his treasons.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Openly; ingenuously; plainly; unreservedly;
undisguisedly; sincerely; candidly; artlessly; freely; readily;
unhesitatingly; liberally; willingly.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Frank-marriage</ent>⟦br⟧
